{
  "texts": [
    "Human Evaluation Framework for Diagnosis Generation DevelopmentThe human evaluation was split into two parts: (1) Diagnostic Accuracy Evaluation; and (2) Diagnostic Reasoning Evaluation.",
    "The Diagnostic Accuracy part was benchmarked against the validated revised SaferDx instrument [21] that incorporates metrics for diagnostic error and safety.",
    "We defined a medical diagnosis using the Medical Subject Headings (MeSH) and National Cancer Institute (NCI) definitions from the National Library of Medicine Unified Medical Language System (UMLS).",
    "The MESH definition states, \"The determination of the nature of a disease or condition, or the distinguishing of one disease or condition from another.",
    "Assessment may be made through physical examination, laboratory tests, or the like.\""
  ]
}